「The
Cove」甫獲得[奧斯卡最佳記錄片獎](http://www.japantoday.com/category/entertainment/view/the-
cove-wins-oscar-for-best-documentary
"http://www.japantoday.com/category/entertainment/view/the-cove-wins-oscar-
for-best-documentary")，讓全球大眾及媒體關注鯨魚殺戮問題，幾天後，反捕鯨團體「海牧人」（Sea Shapherd）領導人Peter
Bethune便在東京[被捕](http://news.brisbanetimes.com.au/breaking-news-world/sea-
shepherd-antiwhaling-activist-arrested-in-japan-20100312-q2y1.html
"http://news.brisbanetimes.com.au/breaking-news-world/sea-shepherd-
antiwhaling-activist-arrested-in-
japan-20100312-q2y1.html")，再度引燃日本與澳洲及紐西蘭之間的爭議。

日本指控他於二月違法侵入日籍捕鯨船，而他則聲稱是要實行公民逮捕權，告發捕鯨船船長一個月前撞沉該組織船隻（全球之聲作者Kevin
Rennie先前[已有報導](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/08/australia-whaling-
war-of-words/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/08/australia-whaling-
war-of-words/")）。

